      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While healthy national pride is a positive force for social cohesion, it is not a neutral concept; it inherently carries the potential to justify exclusionary policies and authoritarianism when it overrides individual rights. The danger lies not in the existence of national identity itself, but in how societies choose to define and enforce that identity, often leading to the suppression of dissent and the marginalization of minorities. Therefore, nationalism is not inherently dangerous, but it is a tool that can be wielded either to build a cohesive society or to dismantle it, depending entirely on the values and power structures in place.",
